{"word":"ἀμαυρόω","slug":"ἀμαυρόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀμαυρόω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>from <a href='S:ἀμαυρός'><el>ἀμαυρός</el></a>\n<p/><i>to make dim, faint</i>, or <i>obscure</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>; <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to impair</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to become dim, suffer eclipse</i>, of the sun, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>; <i>to disappear</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b><p/>"}]}